==English==
===Noun===
'''blaze''', plural '''[[blazes]]'''

# a fire, especially a fast-burning fire producing a lot of flames and light
# a mark resembling a fire
#: "The [[palomino]] had a white blaze on its face."

===Verb===
'''blaze''', '''[[blazing]]''', '''[[blazed]]'''

====Intransitive====

# to be on fire, especially producing a lot of flames and light
#: "The campfire blazed merrily."

====Transitive====

# cut a path through vegetation, or metaphorically through any difficulty
#: "The [[guide]] blazed his way through the [[undergrowth]]."
#: "Darwin blazed a path for the rest of us."

